ANALISI ESPLORATIVA 2

RNFL average using visit2 as time

## define base for the graphs and store in object 'p'
p <- ggplot(data = Gdata[!is.na(RNFL_average),], aes(x = visit2, y = RNFL_average,  color= factor(Patient) )  )
p + geom_line() + geom_point() +
     geom_smooth(method = lm, color="black")

mean_RNFL_thickness using visit2 as time

## define base for the graphs and store in object 'p'
p <- ggplot(data = Gdata[!is.na(RNFL_average),], aes(x = visit2, y = mean_RNFL_thickness,  color= factor(Patient) )  )
p + geom_line() + geom_point() +
     geom_smooth(method = lm, color="black")

IOP (intra-ocular pressure). From now on visit2 is used as time.

## define base for the graphs and store in object 'p'
p <- ggplot(data = Gdata[!is.na(RNFL_average),], aes(x = visit2, y = IOP,  color= factor(Patient) )  )
p + geom_line() + geom_point() +
     geom_smooth(method = lm, color="black")
